  ('7f1a601f-f4f6-54c4-ae96-1dc6996034d4', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Stoneware Powder Glazes', 'P2541', 'Rustic Green Powder Glaze', 'Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Different effects can be achieved with the Potterycrafts Rustic Green Oxidising Powder Glaze. Variable thickness and different heating and cooling, especially on embossed ware. Temperature Range: 1220-1260°C. Gives brighter results when used on whiter firing bodies. Simple to apply for both beginners and advanced potters.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Rustic-Green-Powder-Glaze_7c597460-781c-4fb5-adc7-729f50fa4b2c.jpg?v=1722584816', null, 'Green', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-rustic-green-powder-glaze'),
  ('706c2267-bb77-5f6e-a30d-82ba0ea84a22', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Stoneware Powder Glazes', 'P2302', 'Taggs Yard Reactive Stoneware Slip', 'Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Potterycrafts Taggs Reactive Slip has been designed by Harry Horlock-Stringer of the Taggs Yard School of Ceramics to create effects similar to those that would be obtained from a flame fired reduction firing. Different thickness of slip and glaze, as well as a variation in firing temperature can produce remarkable effects in finished ware, such as obtaining blue, black, green, and orange from the same slip application. Temperature Range: 1260-1280°C. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Simple to apply for both beginners and advanced potters. The image shown is P2300 Chun Tenmoku glaze layered over P2302 reactive slip.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Taggs-Yard-Reactive-Slip_98ef4486-6466-43b4-a120-5dd420b476d5.jpg?v=1721299016', null, null, 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-taggs-yard-reactive-stoneware-slip'),
