  ('19e57887-d096-57b2-a974-9bab43108296', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4289', 'Post Office Red Leaded Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts Post Office Red is a leaded powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Leaded Colour (powder) Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 760-800°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 780-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Post-Office-Red-Leaded-Powder-On-Glaze.jpg?v=1720776028', null, 'Red', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-post-office-red-leaded-powder-on-glaze'),
  ('e22c8bb3-583a-5026-bd0e-50dfc51554e6', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Earthenware Powder Glazes', 'P2253', 'Green Celadon Reduction Powder Glaze', 'Cone 06 / Cone 04', 'Potterycrafts Green Celadon reduction glaze that will run thickly into carved or fluted surfaces. To achieve the green colour this glaze must be fired in reducing conditions. In oxidizing fire, it will be a pale amber colour. Temperature Range: 1260-1290°C. Simple to apply for both beginners and advanced potters.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Green-Celadon-Reduction-Powder-Glaze.jpg?v=1727875173', null, 'Green', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-green-celadon-reduction-powder-glaze'),
