  ('cffccc69-601d-5de7-89ae-3b087aab9e1f', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4349', 'Green Blue Leadfree Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts Green Blue is a lead-free powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 780-820°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 800-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Green-Blue-Leadfree-Powder-On-Glaze_46ffad64-3d9d-42c4-854c-d9a8d5512d11.jpg?v=1727875848', null, 'Green, Blue', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-green-blue-leadfree-powder-on-glaze'),
  ('63e67c65-4fa2-534a-91ef-76079035c1e1', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4344', 'Raised Paste White Leadfree Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts Raised Paste White is a lead-free powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 780-820°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 800-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Raised-Paste-White-Leadfree-Powder-On-Glaze.jpg?v=1720776317', null, 'White', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-raised-paste-white-leadfree-powder-on-glaze'),
  ('ab0b54b8-6f69-5c1f-bedd-0ad109276d34', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4346', 'White Leadfree Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts White is a lead-free powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 780-820°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 800-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-White-Leadfree-Powder-On-Glaze_3692a45c-5303-4164-9e37-bf5413419cdc.jpg?v=1727875162', null, 'White', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-white-leadfree-powder-on-glaze'),
  ('35d175eb-3a2c-5350-802f-cc22ff088af9', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Earthenware Powder Glazes', 'P2221', 'David Leach Tenmoku Powder Glaze', 'Cone 06 / Cone 04', 'Potterycrafts David Leach Tenmoku gives is best fired on iron-bearing body with a short period of oxidisation at the end of firing, to bring out characteristic rusty colour on thin edges. The glaze is very nice over fluted or engraved decoration. Temperature Range: 1280-1300°C. Non-toxic (lead-free) Please follow manufacturer instructions. Simple to apply for both beginners and advanced potters.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-David-Leach-Tenmoku-Powder-Glaze_c3f3bd31-2c77-4f2f-9ad5-528631cd0f42.jpg?v=1722584765', null, null, 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-david-leach-tenmoku-powder-glaze'),
  ('dac203b5-db4a-530b-943a-dd7b49bc1cb3', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Stoneware Powder Glazes', 'P2220', 'David Leach Jade Green Celadon Powder Glaze', 'Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Potterycrafts David Leach Jade Green Celadon gives Chinese celadon when reduced, honey when oxidised, and is shiny at 1280°C. The glaze is very nice over fluted or engraved decoration. Temperature Range: 1250-1280°C. Non-toxic (lead-free) Please follow manufacturer instructions. Simple to apply for both beginners and advanced potters.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-David-Leach-Jade-Green-Celadon-Powder-Glaze.jpg?v=1727875846', 'Glossy', 'Green', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-david-leach-jade-green-celadon-powder-glaze'),
  ('0b75cb35-176f-5b61-8edc-72babeb25c42', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Stoneware Powder Glazes', 'P2576', 'Nordic Blue Mist Powder Glaze', 'Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'The Nordic Blue Mist Powder glaze has been specially developed by Potterycrafts to bring reactive glazes to our customers. A diverse array of outcomes can be produced from the same glaze by differing the application style and variable glaze thickness in our powder glazes and all the glazes within the Nordic range can be over laid to create unique results. Different rates of heating and cooling within the firing can achieve an array of outcomes, especially on embossed ware. Temperature Range: 1200 - 1240°C. Colour: Blue. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Vertical form - fired on standard Porcelain - 1240°C. Mixing instructions to produce a dipping glaze. For every 1kg of powder add 650mls of water. Because these powders contain a small addition of a glaze binder it is necessary to allow the mixture to stand overnight to allow the binder to dissolve and be absorbed. Then mix and blend the glaze together before sieving through a 60’s-80’s mesh sieve. Depending on the porosity of the biscuit it may be necessary to add more water to produce a satisfactory dipping glaze.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Nordic-Blue-Mist-Powder-Glaze.jpg?v=1728662315', null, 'Blue', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-nordic-blue-mist-powder-glaze'),
  ('9e57ecbb-636f-58a0-a287-852659669bc4', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Stoneware Powder Glazes', 'P2593', 'Nordic Royal Azure Blue Powder Glaze', 'Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'The Nordic Royal Azure Powder glaze has been specially developed by Potterycrafts to bring reactive glazes to our customers. A diverse array of outcomes can be produced from the same glaze by differing the application style and variable glaze thickness in our powder glazes and all the glazes within the Nordic range can be over laid to create unique results. Different rates of heating and cooling within the firing can achieve an array of outcomes, especially on embossed ware. Temperature Range: 1200 - 1240°C. Colour: Dark Blue. Non-toxic (lead-free)– Perfect for tableware. Please follow manufacturer instructions. Vertical form - fired on standard Porcelain - 1240°C. Mixing instructions to produce a dipping glaze. For every 1kg of powder add 650mls of water. Because these powders contain a small addition of a glaze binder it is necessary to allow the mixture to stand overnight to allow the binder to dissolve and be absorbed. Then mix and blend the glaze together before sieving through a 60’s-80’s mesh sieve. Depending on the porosity of the biscuit it may be necessary to add more water to produce a satisfactory dipping glaze.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Nordic-Royal-Azure-Blue-Powder-Glaze_93851638-230b-4c98-80f9-86d467c8ca39.jpg?v=1727875158', null, 'Blue', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-nordic-royal-azure-blue-powder-glaze'),
  ('718dbb0e-47f4-548e-8716-49f981ed8f0b', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4287', 'Pacific Coral Leaded Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts Pacific Coral is a leaded powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Leaded Colour (powder) Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 760-800°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 780-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Pacific-Coral-Leaded-Powder-On-Glaze.jpg?v=1720775693', null, 'Coral', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-pacific-coral-leaded-powder-on-glaze'),
