  ('7d58d883-75be-52db-8cf9-8e569e1cc1d1', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'On-Glaze Colours', 'P4274', 'Sepia Brown Leaded Powder On-Glaze', 'Cone 018 / Cone 016', 'Potterycrafts Sepia Brown is a leaded powder glaze. Powdered colours can be used for China painting or screen printing depending on the chosen medium. Powders should be thoroughly mixed into a medium on a glass slab with a palette knife. The approximate ratio is 2-part colours to 1 part medium. Leaded Colour (powder) Temperature Range for earthenware, tile and bone China: 760-800°C. Temperature Range for porcelain: 780-840°C.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Sepia-Brown-Leaded-Powder-On-Glaze.jpg?v=1720772298', null, 'Brown', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-sepia-brown-leaded-powder-on-glaze'),
  ('cf554ec6-e72c-5342-96c7-439ae1cd1d2d', 'commercial', 'Potterycrafts', 'Underglazes', 'P4521', 'Dark Pink Powder Underglaze', 'Cone 06 / Cone 6', 'Dark Pink Powdered coloured underglaze should be mixed with a suitable medium in the approximate proportions of 2 parts colour to 1 part medium. These can be diluted further with water for air brush application. Maximum Firing Temperature - 1280°C Recommended mediums are: P4479 - Underglaze medium - A water-based gum medium, suitable for all applications. P4264 - Universal medium - A water-based medium which gives a creamy, slow drying colour mixture and is best suited for hand painting. P4256- Fat Oil and P4261 China Painters Turps - A combination of these two (approximately half/half) mixed with underglaze colours give a slow drying mixture for painting onto bisque ware. IMPORTANT - Note that when using this medium you must harden the colours to 800°C before glazing.', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0865/4399/1066/files/Potterycrafts-Dark-Pink-Powder-Underglaze.jpg?v=1727875802', null, 'Pink', 'https://potterycrafts.co.uk/products/potterycrafts-dark-pink-powder-underglaze'),
